main event: On December 31, 1956, in Guam, an AF Interceptor Pilot reported a ground-radar sighting of a UFO passing under his aircraft, with blinking white lights, maneuvering in ways that indicate an aircraft but without positive visibility or stated radial ability of the observer.
interesting points: The UFO was described as dime-sized with blinking white lights.
It passed under the pilot's aircraft, then came over the pilot, and later turned west then south before coming over the pilot again.
The pilot was unable to gain contact with the UFO.
The pilot had to break off the encounter due to low fuel.
Maneuvers strongly indicated an aircraft, but no positive visibility was established.
sighted object: a UFO with blinking white lights
